title: ‘Clash of culture’ leads to rapid increase in sexual crimes within the UK
description: Reform UK Leader Nigel Farage is appalled by the increase in sexual crime and Islamic extremism.  “He was released by accident,” Mr Farage told Sky News host Paul Murray.  “Every single week now, we get these accounts of young men of fighting age crossing the English Channel, causing huge degrees of harm within our communities.  “A lot of these men come from countries in which women are not even second-class citizens, and that’s the clash of culture.”

title: ‘Frightening scenes’: Dangerous Islamic extremism in the UK
description: Reform UK Leader Nigel Farage is frightened by brazen Islamic extremist groups.  “I hope the left finally wake up, that actually there is something even more dangerous than identity politics that is going on,” Mr Farage told Sky News host Paul Murray.  “I thought the scenes that I witnessed … were simply the most frightening scenes that I have ever, ever seen.  “This is why we have to be very, very careful about who we, both in this and your country, let in.

title: ‘Election integrity is low’: ‘Problematic’ numbers at California polling stations
description: Sky News Contributor Kosha Gada explains why nobody’s turning out to vote in California.  “There's a big chunk of the California electorate … that just doesn’t feel inspired by any of the options,” Ms Gada told Sky News host Rita Panahi.   “Trust in elections and election integrity is low.  “That is a very problematic thing for democracy.”

title: Democrats ‘deny’ comparing Trump to Hitler despite incriminating videos
description: Sky News contributor Kosha Gada criticises Democrats lying about making Hitler comparisons to US President Donald Trump despite video evidence.  “I think cause they’re out of options,” Ms Gada told Sky News host Rita Panahi.   “They don’t have the option to rewrite history.  “They only have one option left, which is to deny it.”

title: ‘Crocodile tears’: Mamdani caught in a lie by internet sleuths
description: Sky News contributor Kosha Gada calls out New York City mayoral candidate Zohran Mamdani for being caught in a lie.  “Next, it will be his neighbour's pet,” Ms Gada told Sky News host Rita Panahi.   “The internet is incredible at finding these things out.  “He with those crocodile tears … He really is an actor … a very good one.”

title: Mamdani ‘likened to Obama’ for ‘cheap tricks’
description: Sky News contributor Kosha Gada likens Zohran Mamdani to Obama in his political tactics.  “He doesn’t need to do these cheap tricks,” Ms Gada told Sky News host Rita Panahi.   “He has vast political ambitions.   “Many people have likened him to Obama.  “Very conveniently using one side of his heritage.”

title: ‘Consulting widely’: Coalition continues deliberations on net zero
description: Shadow Energy Minister Dan Tehan presents the Coalition's ongoing deliberations on achieving net zero by 2050.  Mr Tehan emphasised the need for thorough consultations with colleagues and industry before finalising a position.   With 5,000 jobs at Tomago now at risk due to rising energy prices, Tehan urges Prime Minister Anthony Albanese to reassure workers about their future and suggests energy affordability is crucial for sustainability.

title: Trump ‘hijacked’ the party: He won’t run for a third term
description: Sky News contributor Kosha Gada addresses the media’s obsession with US President Donald Trump serving a third term.  “He has completely remade the party. It started as a hijack,” Ms Gada told Sky News host Rita Panahi.  “They’re generally following in his footsteps.  “It would be funny, he’d never do this.”

title: The next US president could be ‘someone outside of the government’
description: Sky News contributor Kosha Gada names contenders for the next US president.  “There are young people that are just great at doing battle,” Ms Gada told Sky News host Rita Panahi.  “There could even be someone outside of government that we don’t quite think about today that is just one orbit outside."

title: ‘Destined for great things’: Barron Trump could be president one day
description: Sky News host Rita Panahi stokes predictions Barron Trump could be president one day.  “There's also talk about Donald Trump Jr being the next one up,” Ms Panahi said.   “There are people already having bets on Barron Trump being president one day.  “He’s only 18 but possibly destined for great things.”

title: Coalition must hold the government ‘to account’ for their ‘shambles’ energy policy
description: Shadow Energy Minister Dan Tehan details the underlying factors around the Coalition’s net zero policy discussions.  “Already the colleagues are absolutely committed to making sure we can throw all technology at our energy supply,” Mr Tehan told Sky News host Sharri Markson.  “Including nuclear, they are very committed.”

title: ‘Line after line blacked out’: Chris Bowen’s redacted climate booklet
description: Sky News host Paul Murray refreshes the “important part” of Energy Minister Chris Bowen’s secret briefing.

title: ‘They argue constantly’: Nigel Farage not concerned about tactical voting
description: Reform UK Leader Nigel Farage is not concerned about tactical voting.  “It might hurt us here and there,” Mr Farage told Sky News host Paul Murray.  “They argue with each other constantly … so to get them to be organised across 600 constituencies.   “I really don’t think that they’ve got the ability to organise this nationwide.”

title: ‘I am not done’: Kamala Harris believes ‘history is calling her’ to the presidency
description: Sky News host Paul Murray says Kamala Harris believes “history is still calling her” as she looks to run for presidency again.

title: ‘On her own two feet’: Lidia Thorpe defends threat to burn Parliament House
description: On tonight’s episode of Paul Murray Live, Sky News host Paul Murray analyses Lidia Thorpe, Chris Bowen, US politics and more.
